    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Order containing around 425 species in 3 families of rapid-flying birds that feed in flight upon insects or nectar, having a 'hand' and primary flight feathers constituting a relatively great proportion of the wing, and relatively weak feet used primarily only for perching.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
